1. Ja se sa tim *ne slažem*. (I don't agree with that.)
2. Ti se *slažeš* sa mnom, zar ne? (You agree with me, don't you?)
3. Oni se *nisu slagali* oko toga šta treba uraditi. (They didn't agree on what should be done.)
4. Kada se *slože* sve kockice, dobiće se slika. (When all the puzzle pieces fit together, you get a picture.)
5. Molim te, *složi* ovu hrpu papira po abecednom redu. (Please, sort this pile of papers alphabetically.)
6. Nisam siguran kako da *se složim* sa njim oko ovoga. (I'm not sure how to agree with him on this.)
7. Oni su *se složili* da rade zajedno na projektu. (They agreed to work together on the project.)
8. Kada se *složimo* oko uslova, možemo da potpišemo ugovor. (When we agree on the terms, we can sign the contract.)
9. Njih dvoje se *slažu* kao braća. (Those two get along like brothers.)
10. Nadam se da će se stvari *složiti* u našu korist. (I hope things will fall into place in our favor.)